</figureCitation>
) straight and thick, fore tibiae (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1217,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1124,1147]" captionTargetBox="[175,1420,208,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[158,1428,193,1104]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 20. Legs of Xiphovelia spp. (males). 11 – 14. fore leg (11. X. glauca Esaki &amp; Miyamoto, 1959; 12. X. denigrata sp. nov.; 13. X. fulva sp. nov.; 14. X. reflexa sp. nov.); Scale 0.2 mm; 15 – 18. middle leg (15. X. glauca Esaki &amp; Miyamoto, 1959; 16. X. denigrata sp. nov.; 17. X. fulva sp. nov.; 18. X. reflexa sp. nov.); Scale 0.2 mm; 19. fore tibia of X. denigrata sp. nov. (male); Scale 0.1 mm; 20. second middle tarsus of X. denigrata sp. nov. (male); Scale 0.1 mm. gc: grasping comb; cl: claw; va: ventral arolium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244015/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="197">
Fig. 
<number box="[1188,1217,728,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="197" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) slightly curved in apical part, length of grasping comb 
<number box="[588,640,764,788]" pageId="7" pageNumber="197" value="0.1">0.10</number>
, about 
<number box="[729,778,764,788]" pageId="7" pageNumber="197" value="0.29">0.29</number>
