<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="197" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1904]" pageId="7" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1807,1832]" pageId="7" pageNumber="197">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[838,905,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="197">fulvus</emphasis>
means yellowish brown, refers to head dorsum of apterous male almost yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
